1 SECTION 4. AMENDATORY 59 O.S. 2021, Section 493.4, is
2 amended to read as follows:
3 Section 493.4. A. No person who is granted a special license
4 or a special training license shall practice outside the limitations
5 of the license.
6 B. To be eligible for special or special training licensure,
7 the applicant shall have completed all the requirements for full and
8 unrestricted medical licensure except graduate education and/or,
9 licensing examination, or other requirements relative to the basis
10 for the special license or special training license.
11 C. By rule, the State Board of Medical Licensure and
12 Supervision shall establish restrictions for special and special
13 training licensure to assure that the holder will practice only
14 under appropriate circumstances as set by the Board.
15 D. A special license or special training license shall be
16 renewable annually upon the approval of the Board and upon the
17 evaluation of performance in the special circumstances upon which
18 the special license or special training license was granted.
19 E. The issuance of a special license or a special training
20 license shall not be construed to imply that a full and unrestricted
21 medical license will be issued at a future date.
22 F. All other provisions of the Oklahoma Allopathic Medical and
23 Surgical Licensure and Supervision Act shall apply to holders of
24 special licenses or special training licenses.
ENGR. S. B. NO. 1651 Page 18

1 G. This section shall not limit the authority of any state
2 agency or educational institution in this state which employs a
3 special or special training specially licensed physician to impose
4 additional practice limitations upon such physician.
5 SECTION 5. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
6 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 493.4a of Title 59, unless there
7 is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
8 A. No person who is granted a special training license for
9 postgraduate training shall practice outside the limitations of the
10 license.
11 B. To be eligible for a special training license for
12 postgraduate training, the applicant shall have completed all the
13 requirements for full and unrestricted medical licensure except
14 graduate education, licensing examination, or other requirements
15 relative to the basis for the special training license.
16 C. By rule, the State Board of Medical Licensure and
17 Supervision shall establish restrictions for a special training
18 license for postgraduate training to assure that the holder will
19 practice only under appropriate circumstances as set by the Board.
20 D. A special training license for postgraduate training shall
21 be renewable annually upon the approval of the Board Secretary and
22 upon the evaluation of performance in the special circumstances upon
23 which the special training license was granted.
24
ENGR. S. B. NO. 1651 Page 19

1 E. The issuance of a special training license for postgraduate
2 training shall not be construed to imply that a full and
3 unrestricted medical license will be issued at a future date.
4 F. All other provisions of the Oklahoma Allopathic Medical and
5 Surgical Licensure and Supervision Act shall apply to holders of
6 special training licenses for postgraduate training.
7 G. This section shall not limit the authority of any state
8 agency or educational institution in this state which employs a
9 person licensed under this section to impose additional practice
10 limitations upon such physician.
11 SECTION 6. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
12 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 493.5b of Title 59, unless there
13 is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
14 The holder of a full and unrestricted license may choose at any
15 time to retire and apply for physician emeritus licensure status by
16 notifying the State Board of Medical Licensure and Supervision.
17 There shall be no fee associated with obtaining or maintaining
18 physician emeritus licensure status. An applicant for a physician
19 emeritus license shall apply in a manner required by the Board.
