3 SECTION 10. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
4 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 530.1 of Title 59, unless there
5 is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
6 A. The State Board of Medical Licensure and Supervision is
7 authorized to obtain a national criminal history background check as
8 a condition of eligibility for individuals seeking licensure to
9 practice as an athletic trainer for initial licensure in this state
10 and pursuant to the provisions of an athletic trainer compact as a
11 condition for initial licensure.
12 B. Applicant fingerprints shall be submitted to the Oklahoma
13 State Bureau of Investigation (OSBI) and the national criminal
14 history background check shall be conducted in accordance with
15 Section 150.9 of Title 74 of the Oklahoma Statutes. OSBI shall
16 return national criminal history results to the Board.
17 C. Results obtained from the national criminal history
18 background check shall be used solely for the screening of athletic
19 trainer applicants and shall be retained by the Board. The Board
20 shall not disseminate criminal history record information resulting
21 from the background check.
22 SECTION 11. AMENDATORY 59 O.S. 2021, Section 531, is
23 amended to read as follows:
24
ENGR. S. B. NO. 1651 Page 24

1 Section 531. A. A Beginning January 1, 2027, a license issued
