3 SECTION 13. AMENDATORY 59 O.S. 2021, Section 534, is
4 amended to read as follows:
5 Section 534. A. Any person actively engaged as an athletic
6 trainer in this state on the effective date of this act shall,
7 within six (6) months of that date, be issued a license if proof is
8 submitted of five (5) years’ experience as an athletic trainer
9 within the preceding ten-year period, and the license fee required
10 by the Oklahoma Athletic Trainers Act is paid. Nothing herein in
11 the Oklahoma Athletic Trainers Act shall be construed to require any
12 educational institution or other bona fide athletic organization to
13 use the services of a licensed athletic trainer.
14 B. Athletic trainers shall not misrepresent in any manner,
15 either directly or indirectly, their skills, training, professional
16 credentials, identity or services.
17 C. Any person, as authorized in accordance with Section 5 of
18 Title 76 of the Oklahoma Statutes, may offer prevention, emergency
19 care or first aid services on a voluntary, uncompensated basis, to
20 any amateur or group at an amateur athletic event.
