3 SECTION 16. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
4 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 888.7A of Title 59, unless there
5 is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
6 A. The State Board of Medical Licensure and Supervision is
7 authorized to obtain a national criminal history background check as
8 a condition of eligibility for individuals seeking licensure to
9 practice as an occupational therapist for initial licensure in this
10 state and pursuant to the provisions of an occupational therapy
11 licensure compact as a condition for initial licensure.
12 B. Applicant fingerprints shall be submitted to the Oklahoma
13 State Bureau of Investigation (OSBI) and the national criminal
14 history background check shall be conducted in accordance with
15 Section 150.9 of Title 74 of the Oklahoma Statutes. OSBI shall
16 return national criminal history results to the Board.
17 C. Results obtained from the national criminal history
18 background check shall be used solely for the screening of
19 occupational therapist applicants and shall be retained by the
20 Board. The Board shall not disseminate criminal history record
21 information resulting from the background check.
22 SECTION 17. AMENDATORY 59 O.S. 2021, Section 889.5, is
23 amended to read as follows:
24
ENGR. S. B. NO. 1651 Page 29

1 Section 889.5. A. Except as otherwise provided by law, the
2 State Board of Medical Licensure and Supervision shall issue a
3 license to an applicant for a music therapy license when such
4 applicant has completed and submitted an application upon a form and
5 in such manner as the Board prescribes, accompanied by applicable
6 fees, and evidence satisfactory to the Board that the applicant:
7 1. Is at least eighteen (18) years of age;
8 2. Holds a bachelor’s degree or higher in music therapy, or its
9 equivalent, from a program approved by the American Music Therapy
10 Association or any successor organization within an accredited
11 college or university;
12 3. Successfully completed a minimum of one thousand two hundred
13 (1,200) hours of clinical training, with at least fifteen percent
14 (15%) or one hundred eighty (180) hours in preinternship pre-
15 internship experiences, and at least seventy-five percent (75%) or
16 nine hundred (900) hours in internship experiences. Internship
17 programs may be approved by an academic institution, the American
18 Music Therapy Association, or both;
19 4. Is in good standing based on a review of the applicant’s
20 music therapy licensure history in other jurisdictions, including a
21 review of any alleged misconduct or neglect in the practice of music
22 therapy on the part of the applicant; and
23 5. Passed the examination for board certification offered by
24 the Certification Board for Music Therapists or any successor
ENGR. S. B. NO. 1651 Page 30

1 orga nization or provides proof of being transitioned into board
2 certification, and the applicant is currently a board-certified
3 music therapist.
4 B. The State Board of Medical Licensure and Supervision shall
5 issue a music therapy license to an applicant when such applicant
6 has completed and submitted an application upon a form and in such
7 manner as the Board prescribes, accompanied by applicable fees, and
8 evidence satisfactory to the Board that the applicant is licensed
9 and in good standing as a music therapist in another jurisdiction
10 where the qualifications required are equal to or greater than those
11 required in this act the Music Therapy Practice Act at the date of
12 application.
13 C. The Board shall waive the examination requirement until
14 January 1, 2020, for an applicant who is designated as a registered
15 music therapist, certified music therapist or advanced certified
16 music therapist and in good standing with the National Music Therapy
17 Registry.
18 D. The State Board of Medical Licensure and Supervision Board
19 may authorize the Board Secretary to issue a temporary license to
20 practice under the supervision of an Oklahoma licensed music
21 therapist prior to licensure, provided all requirements for
22 licensure have been met and verified. The temporary license shall
23 terminate on the date of the next Board meeting at which the
24 applicant may be considered for a license.
ENGR. S. B. NO. 1651 Page 31

1 E. The Board may, upon notice and opportunity for a hearing,
2 deny an application for reinstatement of a license or reinstate the
